When a user connects to the server through the webpage, the server initiates a WebSocket connection, allowing for the exchange of messages in both directions. This enables the server to send updates or notifications to the client in real-time, while also enabling the client to send requests or input back to the server.

To achieve this, you can leverage Socket.IO's built-in support for WebSockets by setting up a connection listener on the server-side, which establishes a WebSocket connection whenever a client connects. On the client-side, you would then create a Socket.IO instance, which handles the WebSocket connection and provides methods for sending and receiving messages.

